<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-021-892  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 021 892.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DBMS  Nov 1989 v2 n12 p53(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Modernizing the ancient scroll: PD_SCRL consolidates scrollinginquiries for all Dbase dialects. (tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schickler, Peter; Lavigne, Douglas.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>This tutorial focuses on a new method for scrolling through Dbasefiles to find a particular record.andP;  Scrolling, or using 'picklists,' is not new, but most such programs are limited to oneparticular type of input field or file.andP;  This means that programsare becoming bloated with repetitive coding for each desiredscroll.andP;  What PD_SCRL does is replace the repetitious code ofmultiple scrolling pick list variations with a single procedure.andO;PD_SCRL uses parameters to define the scroll, meaning that onlyone instance of scroller code for each complete system is needed.andO;PD_SCRL also uses an alphabetic search that allowssuccessive-single character searches until the desired choice isfound.andP;  This tutorial examines each aspect of PD_SCRL and includescode listings.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   dBASE (Data base management system) (programming).andO;Topic:     TutorialType-In ProgramsScrollingData Base Management SystemsApplications Programming.andO;Feature:   illustrationprogram.andO;Caption:   CASE statements. (program)Code master file. (program)Multiple indexes. (program)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>